                   "message":  "feat(dispatch): Claude active safety-guard scaffold for autonomous Codex dispatch (dry-run only)\n\nReconfigure the dispatch automation toward the owner-directed roles: Codex plans\n+ selects + executes + control-reviews + auto-publishes (the \"human\"); Claude\nmoves out of the executor seat into a dedicated watch / safety-monitor role that\nrecords every phase, assesses for anomalies, and halts the run with a report if\nsomething is wrong. This is the BUILD + DRY-RUN ONLY first cut -- nothing is armed.\n\nAdds (additive; no existing script touched):\n- Invoke-AiDispatchGuard.ps1 -- the Claude active safety-guard. Records each\n  phase to .ai/dispatch-watch/\u003cid\u003e/{watch.log,events.jsonl}; assesses via\n  deterministic hard rules (protected-branch push, force-push, gate failure,\n  non-zero gate exit, block/needs-human verdict, max-runtime, max-correction-\n  rounds) PLUS a Claude LLM verdict; on abort kills the child process tree and\n  writes abort-report.md. -DryRun drives a hermetic scripted sequence (no real\n  loop, no Claude call, no publish) covering the complete / hard-rule-abort /\n  llm-veto-abort paths.\n- AUTONOMOUS_WATCH.md -- design + safety posture: the role reconfig; that this\n  reverses the human-only merge gate (safety net = AI_DISPATCH_AUTOMATION.md\n  section 18 delegated-human bounds + Codex pass verdict + Claude veto); the\n  precise -Executor codex loop swap as the specced next step; and what is\n  explicitly NOT done (scheduler not registered, -PublishMode main not invoked,\n  no live run).\n\nDistinct from the existing passive read-only Watch-AiDispatch.ps1 dashboard,\nwhich keeps its non-participating contract intact.\n\nValidation: 3 dry-run scenarios green (exit 0/2/2 + correct watch.log /\nevents.jsonl / abort-report.md); PSScriptAnalyzer (repo\nPSScriptAnalyzerSettings.psd1, Error+Warning) 0 findings on the new script;\nPester tools/dispatch-tests 308/308; Rust verify gate unaffected (no Rust\nchange). Not armed; held for explicit human review.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
